<br>
How many threads are there going to be on this one issue? Please try looking around. There are many threads that discuss this issue in great depth, and present all the pros and cons of each choice.<br>
<br>
To Svenuce:<br>
<br>
And how many times am I going to see some fool answer by saying something like 'there is little question anymore'. That is a bogus response and very bad advice indeed to a young magician. If you MUST answer, give a balanced one and one that actually makes sense.<br>
<br>
He/she is level 20, so COH is not going to be an issue for him/her for a LONG time. And the statement about nukes is incorrect, please read other threads, the 'best' nukes are clearly evocation, and are at almost all points in the levelling up process (there are exceptions).<br>
<br>
For high end heavy raiders, Conjure *is* the best choice. For those who are lower level, or those who are even Archmages like myself who do not like raiding very much, Evocation remains the better choice.<br>
<br>
There is and remains a balance, and the decision is mostly affected by playstyle. Before 55, my perosnal view, is Conjuration is a very poor choice. Others disagree.<br>
<br>
But whatever your personal view, a statement like &quot;there is no question&quot; is factually wrong. <p>--------------------------------------<BR><BR>
